Ghana Meteorological Agency’s Rainfall Report Oct. 1-10

-- B y   M o s e s   M o z a r t   D z a w u
-- 
2011-10-13T13:16:30Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-10-13/ghana-meteorological-agency-s-rainfall-report-oct-1-10-table-.html
The following are rainfall figures
for selected areas of  Ghana , the world’s second-biggest cocoa
producer, from Oct. 1 to Oct. 10, according to the  Ghana 
Meteorological Agency.  The Western region, which includes the towns of Sefwi
Bekwai and Bogoso, is Ghana’s largest growing area for the
chocolate ingredient, accounting for 55.3 percent of output,
according to the Ghana Cocoa Board.  The Ashanti region accounts for 17.9 percent of production,
while Brong Ahafo generates 9.3 percent, the Eastern region 8.6
percent and the Central region 8.8 percent. Volta accounts for
0.1 percent, the board said.  Ivory Coast , which neighbors Ghana, is the world’s largest
cocoa producer.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Moses Mozart Dzawu in Accra at 
 mdzawu@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
